719423f-a.title: Manhattan: East Broadway - Jefferson Street
719423f-a.text:
East Broadway (left), east from but not including Jefferson Street,
showing a general view of the surrounding area with the Williamsburg
Bridge in the background. This view is from the Jewish Daily Porward
Building, 173-175 East Broadway, south side, between Rutgers and Jefferson
Streets.
February 14, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
719423f-a.folder: East Broadway & Jefferson Street, Manhattan, NY

719421f-b.title: Manhattan: East Broadway - Jefferson Street
719421f-b.text:
East Broadway, north side, east across Jefferson
Street, showing on the far side of same, the Seward
Park branch of the New York Public Library. Incident-
ally, Jefferson Street parallels East Broadway, tho
this short portion at it's terminus retains that iden-
tity. Cn the left is P portion of the Park that has
given it's name to this structure.
June 23, 1939
No's. 1-2
